Program: Outlook
Title: 10/08/2009
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p003vdcp
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 10 Aug 2009
Personal stories behind the news from all over the world. With Valerie Sanderson. On today's programme: Education theft in China; Brazilian cuckolds bar; Sued for music sharing; Child chicken farmer. Stolen education in China Dozens of pupils in central China are being robbed of their education because the envelope containing their qualifications has been stolen. We hear from one boy whose future has been blighted. Cuckolds bar in Brazil The BBC's Gary Duffy went along to a bar in Brazil where cuckolds gather to share their experiences of being betrayed. Joel Tennenbaum We hear from the American student who downloaded and distributed music from the internet and now faces paying damages of more than $675,000 to several major record companies. The 11 year-old chicken enthusiast The BBC's Caz Graham visits 11 year-old Daisy who became obsessed with chickens at the age of six and has now developed a thriving chicken and egg enterprise on her parents' farm in the UK. Show less